caption:
&quot;Hi all, check out this event from the 2021 SPAN (The Sexualities Project at Northwestern) Online Workshop, titled &quot;Body Fixes: Entanglements of Sexuality, Disability and Health,&quot; happening on Friday, April 16 from 9am-3 PM CST. It looks amazing!!!

RSVP: Follow the link https://bit.ly/2RcclFP and click on the flyer to register
For more information visit sexualities.northwestern.edu

The following keynote address and presentations include:

Keynote address &quot;Queer History, Disability History, and the Politics of Health&quot;
Regina Kunzel (Princeton University)

Additional presentations by:
&quot;Ed Gein and the Fabrication of the 'Mad Trans Killer&quot;
Ryan Lee Cartwright (University of California, Davis)
&quot;In the heat of the moment: Allergic reactions through fluid exchange&quot;
Michael Gill (Syracuse University)
&quot;The Evidence of Trans Experience (Being Street)&quot;
Jules Gill-Peterson (University of Pittsburgh)
&quot;Beyond Medical Necessity: Transition Related Care and Pharmaceutical Approaches to Sexual Dissatisfaction&quot;
Kristina Gupta (Wake Forest University)

ID: A white flyer decorated by green, blue, yellow and red multicolor gears as borders, with large dark blue title text and a purple text box containing keynote speaker details.&quot;.

